activityList.description: Heart rate was at 140 after half mile. Over 160 with half mile to go. I need a slower start. Monitoring heart rate during the run is helpful.

57 degrees. Cloudy but nice to be out. I can’t remember the last time it was this nice. A red tail hawk flew over the trail. It was carrying some small animal. It landed on a branch to my right and turned to look down at me as I passed.
Wind 24 mph. That was not the route to run.
Not feeling very good but it’s too nice outside.
